This paper involves natural language processing (NLP) techniques for extracting medical concepts from radiology reports, which suggests a strong connection to the cs.CL (Computation and Language) sub-category. Additionally, the paper deals with medical imaging, which is often associated with the cs.CV (Computer Vision) sub-category. The use of machine learning for model development and the focus on accuracy also suggest a connection to the cs.LG (Machine Learning) sub-category. The paper also involves information retrieval techniques for identifying relevant features in the reports, which suggests a connection to the cs.IR (Information Retrieval) sub-category. Finally, the paper deals with medical data, which may involve issues related to privacy and security, suggesting a connection to the cs.CY (Computers and Society) sub-category.
